3 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 23.1-07-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is
4 amended and reenacted as follows:
5 23.1-07-06. Duties of the department.
6 The department shall:
7 1. Hold at least one examination each year, administered by the department or a third-
8 party examination service, at a designated time and place for the purpose of
9 examining candidates for certification.
10 2. Promote the program of certification of water supply and wastewater disposal system
11 operators.
12 3. Distribute notices and applications and to receive and evaluate applications.
13 4. Collect fees for initial certification and annual renewal.
14 5. Prepare, conduct, and grade examinations. The department may use a third-party
15 examination service to prepare, conduct, and grade examinations.
16 6. Maintain records of operator qualifications, certification examination results, and a
17 register of certified operators.
18 7. Promote and schedule regular training schools and programs.
19 8. Adopt rules necessary to carry out this chapter.
20 SECTION 4. AMENDMENT. Section 23.1-07-08 of the North Dakota Century Code is
21 amended and reenacted as follows:
22 23.1-07-08. Violations - Penalty.
23 Any
24 1. A person that violates this chapter, a rule implementing this chapter, or an order issued
25 by the department under this chapter is subject to a civil penalty not to exceed five
26 thousand dollars per day of violation.
27 2. A person violatingthat willfully violates this chapter or the rules adopted under this
28 chapter, after written notice of the violation by the department, is guilty of a class A
29 misdemeanor.
30 3. A person that willfully makes a false statement, representation, or certification in an
31 application, record, report, plan, or other document filed or required to be maintained
